  VALUES (7, 'AUA: CRPC', NULL, 0.00, 200.00, 'M', '{"sidePanelText": "", "id": 4, "name": "Prostate Cancer", "triggers": [], "children": [{"sidePanelText": "<p><span style=\"color:rgb(70, 87, 102); font-family:helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:13.63636302948px\">&bull; Check PSA every 1 &ndash; 3 months</span><br />\n<span style=\"color:rgb(70, 87, 102); font-family:helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:13.63636302948px\">&bull; Conduct Scans every 6 &ndash; 12 months</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Bone Health</strong><br />\n<span style=\"color:rgb(70, 87, 102); font-family:helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:13.63636302948px\">&bull; Calcium Supplementation&nbsp;</span></p>\n", "children": [{"sidePanelText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Provenge</strong></p>\n\n<p>Discuss&nbsp;<strong><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\">Provenge</span></strong><span style=\"color:#FF8C00\">&nbsp;</span>with patients with metastatic CRPC.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div><span style=\"font-family:helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:13.63636302948px\">&bull; Check PSA every 1 &ndash; 3 months</span><br />\n<span style=\"font-family:helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:13.63636302948px\">&bull; Conduct Scans every 6 &ndash; 12 months</span></div>\n", "children": [{"hideChildren": "true", "name": "Painful Bone Mets", "tooltip": "Painful bone metastasis", "sidePanelText": "<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Xofigo</strong></p>\n\n<p>Discuss <span style=\"color:#800080\"><strong>Xofigo </strong></span>with patients with painful bone metastasis.</p>\n", "children": [], "protocol": {"protocol": "<p>&bull; <span style=\"color:#800080\"><strong>Xofigo</strong></span></p>\n\n<p>&bull; Liver monitoring</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Continued monitoring (1-2 mo)</p>\n\n<p>&bull; PSA every 6 months</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Bone Scan</p>\n", "noteToCopy": "<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif; font-size:9.5pt\">In summary, the patient presented with&nbsp;metastatic CRPC and painful bone metastasis.<br />\nManagement Plan:<br />\nPer AUA guidelines*, The patient will receive<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - Xofigo<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - Liver monitoring<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - Continued monitoring (1-2 mo)<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - PSA every 6 months<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - Bone Scan</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif; font-size:9.5pt\">Additionally, research options have been discussed with the patient.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif; font-size:9.5pt\">*Index Patient 5&nbsp; http://www.auanet.org/education/guidelines/castration-resistant-prostate-cancer.cfm</span></p>\n"}}, {"hideChildren": "true", "name": "No Painful Bone Mets", "tooltip": "No painful bone metastasis", "sidePanelText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Zytiga</p>\n\n<p>Discuss&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#008000\">Zytiga&nbsp;</span>with CRPC patients without painful bone metastasis.</p>\n", "children": [], "protocol": {"protocol": "<p>&bull; <span style=\"color:#008000\">Zytiga</span></p>\n\n<p>&bull; Liver monitoring</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Continued monitoring (1-2 mo)</p>\n\n<p>&bull; PSA every 6 months</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Bone Scan</p>\n", "noteToCopy": "<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif; font-size:9.5pt\">In summary, the patient presented with&nbsp;metastatic CRPC and no evidence of painful bone metastasis.<br />\nManagement Plan:<br />\nPer AUA guidelines*, The patient will receive<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - Zytiga<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - Liver monitoring<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - Continued monitoring (1-2 mo)<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - PSA every 6 months<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; - Bone Scan</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif; font-size:9.5pt\">*Index Patient 5&nbsp; http://www.auanet.org/education/guidelines/castration-resistant-prostate-cancer.cfm</span></p>\n"}}], "name": "Metastatic", "hideChildren": "true", "tooltip": "Metastatic CRPC"}, {"sidePanelText": "<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Consider research</strong></p>\n\n<p>For non metastatic prostate cancer, consider&nbsp;<a href=\"https://sites.google.com/a/mavenmedical.net/test/home?previewAsViewer=1&amp;mobile=true\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(66, 139, 202); text-decoration: none; background: 0px 0px;\">research studies</a>.</p>\n", "name": "Non-Metastatic", "tooltip": "Non Metastatic CRPC", "hideChildren": "true", "children": [], "protocol": {"protocol": "<p><span style=\"font-family:helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:13.63636302948px\">&bull; Check PSA every 1 &ndash; 3 months</span><br />\n<span style=\"font-family:helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:13.63636302948px\">&bull; Conduct Scans every 6 &ndash; 12 months</span><br />\n<span style=\"font-family:helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:13.63636302948px\">&bull; <a href=\"https://sites.google.com/a/mavenmedical.net/test/home?previewAsViewer=1&amp;mobile=true\">Consider research</a></span></p>\n", "noteToCopy": "<p>In summary, the patient presented with non-metastatic CRPC.</p>\n\n<p>Management Plan:</p>\n\n<p>Per AUA guidelines*, The patient will receive</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - Continued Androgen Deprivation</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - Observation</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Additionally, research options have been discussed with the patient.</p>\n\n<p>*Index Patient 1&nbsp; http://www.auanet.org/education/guidelines/castration-resistant-prostate-cancer.cfm</p>\n"}}], "name": "CRPC", "hideChildren": "false", "tooltip": "Castration Resistant Prostrate Cancer"}, {"sidePanelText": "<p>When to start ADT:<br />\n&bull; Symptoms related to PC ( hematuria, LUTS, etc)<br />\n&bull; PSA doubling &lt; 9 months<br />\n&bull; Any metastases at presentation<br />\n&bull; PSA &gt;50<br />\n<br />\n1. MA meets with patient to provide injection<br />\n2. Mid Level provider meets with patient to discuss treatment plan</p>\n", "children": [{"hideChildren": "true", "name": "ADT Visit 1", "tooltip": "First Visit for ADT", "sidePanelText": "", "children": [], "protocol": {"protocol": "<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Labs</strong></span><br />\n<strong>Cal, Vitamin D, Albumin, Mag</strong><br />\n&nbsp; &bull; Every year if not NOT denosumab<br />\n&nbsp; &bull; Every 3 &ndash; 6 months if on denosumab<br />\n<strong>PSA</strong><br />\n&nbsp; &bull; 1- 3 months after injection<br />\n&nbsp; &bull;Get Baseline in first 6 months<br />\n&nbsp; &bull;Code Osteop.<br />\n&nbsp; &bull;Yearly while on chronic therapy<br />\n<strong>Testosterone</strong><br />\n&nbsp; &bull; 1 &ndash; 3 months after injection<br />\n&nbsp; &bull;With every injection</p>\n\n<p><font size=\"3\"><span style=\"line-height:25.6000003814697px\"><strong>Dexa Scan</strong></span></font><br />\n&nbsp; &bull;Get Baseline in first 6 months<br />\n&nbsp; &bull;Code Osteop.<br />\n&nbsp; &bull;Yearly while on chronic therapy</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Bone Scan</strong></span><br />\n&nbsp; &bull;Start with PSA of 10, then repeat every doubling of PSA OR every 2 years</p>\n", "noteToCopy": "<p>This is the patient&#39;s first visit for ADT horomone therapy.<br />\nPer the CUA standard protocol, the patient has had the appropriate consultations before the visit.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Treatment plan:</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\">Labs<br />\nCal, Vitamin D, Albumin, Mag<br />\n&nbsp; &bull; Every year if not NOT denosumab<br />\n&nbsp; &bull; Every 3 &ndash; 6 months if on denosumab<br />\nPSA<br />\n&nbsp; &bull; 1- 3 months after injection<br />\n&nbsp; &bull;Get Baseline in first 6 months<br />\n&nbsp; &bull;Code Osteop.<br />\n&nbsp; &bull;Yearly while on chronic therapy<br />\nTestosterone<br />\n&nbsp; --&nbsp;1 &ndash; 3 months after injection<br />\n&nbsp; --With every injection</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\">Dexa Scan<br />\n&nbsp; --Get Baseline in first 6 months<br />\n&nbsp; --Code Osteop.<br />\n&nbsp; --Yearly while on chronic therapy</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\">Bone Scan<br />\n&nbsp; --Start with PSA of 10, then repeat every doubling of PSA OR every 2 years</span></p>\n"}}, {"hideChildren": "true", "name": "ADT Post-Visit 1", "tooltip": "Subsequent to the first visit for ADT therapy", "sidePanelText": "", "children": [], "protocol": {"protocol": "<p><strong>Discuss all lab and treatment results</strong><br />\nWhat to do with the LAB results?<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull; If Vitamin D&lt; 20 give 50,000 IU 2x week for 2 weeks, then recheck<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull; Calcium adjusted &lt; 8.5 double calcium for 6 weeks, recheck<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull; PSA &ndash; if 2 rises despite testosterone &lt; 50 activate CRPC protocol ( see pathway)<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull; If elevated testosterone, consider Casodex and check injection site/techniques<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull; Consider Provenge for eligible patients &ndash; refer to Infusion center<br />\nWhat to do with Bone Scan<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp;If positive, consider&nbsp;<span style=\"color:rgb(139, 69, 19)\"><strong>Xgeva</strong></span><br />\nWhat to do with Dexa Scan<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull; T score &gt;-1 continue maintenance<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull; T score &ndash; 1 -2.5: check Frax score.&nbsp;<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &bull;&nbsp;&gt;3%&nbsp;<strong>hip&nbsp;</strong>fracture risk, start&nbsp;<span style=\"color:rgb(139, 69, 19)\"><strong>Prolia</strong></span><br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &bull;&nbsp;&gt; 20%&nbsp;<strong>total&nbsp;</strong>frracture risk, start&nbsp;<span style=\"color:rgb(139, 69, 19)\"><strong>Prolia</strong></span><br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull; T score &lt; -2.5 start&nbsp;<span style=\"color:rgb(139, 69, 19)\"><strong>Prolia</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>SCHEDULE NEXT OV following injection schedule</strong></p>\n", "noteToCopy": "<p>This is a subsequent encounter for ADT therapy.&nbsp;</p>\n"}}], "name": "Not Castration Resistant", "hideChildren": "true", "tooltip": "Not Castration Resistant"}]}');

